Kenneth L. BALDWIN, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.:2D18-0558 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. December 20, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

This appeal is dismissed as untimely filed, without prejudice to any right Appellant may have to file a motion to correct illegal sentence with respect to the argument raised in claim two of the underlying motion to correct, vacate, and set aside an illegal sentence pursuant to Florida Rules of Criminal Procedure 3.800(a).

KELLY, VILLANTI, and BADALAMENTI, JJ., Concur.
